data.description: Discover the perfect blend of serenity and modern living in this magnificent 2-level home located at 3166 Dupont Pkwy with breath taking  views and colorful sunsets. Nestled within the coveted Appoquinimink School District and the Wallace community, this property offers the ideal setting for comfortable family living. With over 2,100 sq. ft. of living space on the upper level and 1500 on the lower level, this home boasts a partially finished basement with an in law suite with three bedrooms, one full bathroom, and it's own washer and dryer, providing versatility and convenience. The main level features include  an open floor plan, an eat-in kitchen, beamed ceilings and a stone hearth fireplace, four spacious bedrooms and two bathrooms, accommodating all your every need.  Recent updates to this private oasis include a new roof in 2020, new siding in 2021 . Upstairs, fresh carpeting from 2021 adds a touch of elegance to the interior. This home also offers practical updates, including a new well installed in 2017, updated electrical panel boxes with two breakers, and a backup gas generator added in 2021. The driveway was resurfaced in 2021, adding to the overall functionality and aesthetic giving you room for all of your visitors or toys.  Outside, the property sits on a sprawling 3.5-acre lot, featuring inviting river views, providing ample space for outdoor activities and relaxation. A private boat dock with lift grant  and direct access to the river, where within a pleasant 20 minute boat ride,  access the Delaware Bay and beyond, perfect for boating enthusiasts. Additionally, there is a separate garage near the dock fitted with electric and water for additional convenience.  3166 Dupont Pkwy offers the best of both worlds - a spacious and updated interior combined with a serene 3.5-acre lot in a prime location. Don't miss this opportunity to make this exceptional property your new home. Contact us today to schedule a viewing and experience the charm and beauty of 3166 Dupont Pkwy. for yourself.
